## Coding Conventions

{{!-- Define naming conventions, code style, and language-specific rules here --}}
{{!-- Examples:
- TypeScript strict mode required; no `any` types
- Use PascalCase for types/interfaces, camelCase for variables/functions
- Prefer `unknown` over `any` for untyped values
- Use Zod schemas for runtime validation, not TypeScript enums
- One responsibility per file
--}}

## Testing Standards

{{!-- Define testing requirements and patterns here --}}
{{!-- Examples:
- All new features must include unit tests
- Test files mirror source structure: src/foo.ts → test/foo.test.ts
- Use Vitest with global test APIs (describe, it, expect)
- Minimum 80% code coverage for new code
- Tests must validate behavior, not just existence
--}}

